100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On October 14, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, focusing on international peace and security amid rising tensions in Europe. In the United States, the trial of the Scopes "Monkey" case continued to draw national attention, spotlighting the clash between science and religion. Meanwhile, political unrest in Germany and France hinted at shifting alliances in the wake of World War I.
